<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastigera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. hastigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the sagittate or hastate leaves, extended inflorescence with secondary peduncles 2-12 mm long, outer sepals 5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 mm, the corolla tube 2.7-3 cm, the limb deeply lobed, 2.5-3 cm diam. Capsules at least sometimes with a persistent style.
</paragraph>
